cl-pq-covenants
===============

Post-Quantum Covenant Script Patterns for Blockchain Transactions

This software was extracted from the CLPIC project (Common Lisp P2P
Intellectual Property Chain).

Original source: src/blockchain/pq-covenants.lisp

CRYPTOGRAPHIC NOTICE
--------------------

The Dilithium signature implementation included in this package is a STUB
for API compatibility only. It does NOT provide actual cryptographic security.

For production use, you MUST integrate a verified Dilithium implementation
such as:
- liboqs (Open Quantum Safe) via CFFI bindings
- A formally verified implementation

The stub functions will compile and run tests, but signature verification
always returns true. This is intentional for development and testing purposes.

DEPENDENCIES
------------

This package is standalone and requires only:
- SBCL (Steel Bank Common Lisp) or compatible CL implementation
- ASDF (Another System Definition Facility)

No external libraries are required.

STANDARDS COMPLIANCE
--------------------

This implementation follows:
- NIST FIPS 204: ML-DSA (Dilithium) specification
- BIP-341: Taproot sighash design principles
- Bitcoin Covenants: OP_CTV-inspired introspection model
